{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/support-for-adult-carers/diagnosis/identification-of-carers/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"fdbb1671-2bdc-57f0-81c5-e2e9d29e630e","slug":"identification-of-carers","fullItemName":"Identification of carers","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field fe031876-0286-49f1-a23b-ac4000b1e436 --><h2>How can I identify carers?</h2><!-- end field fe031876-0286-49f1-a23b-ac4000b1e436 -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item d0f7cfa0-ba82-4110-a1ef-ac4000b1e436 --><!-- begin field 967dc816-36a2-48a5-bd8b-ac4000b1e436 --><ul><li><strong>Actively seek to identify carers</strong> (in line with the Care Act 2014), using opportunities such as GP appointments, flu jab appointments, and home visits. Ensure policies and systems encourage the identification of carers.<ul><li>Be aware that some people might not view themselves as a carer, or may not ask for support from certain professionals (for example a GP) because they may not view support for carers as part of that professional's role.</li><li>Possible ways to identify carers in general practice (involving the whole practice team) include self-identification, at registration, opportunistic identification, at diagnosis, and on hospital admission or discharge.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Ask a person with care and support needs who helps and supports them</strong> (apart from paid practitioners) — this may not be a family member or someone who lives with the person, and may be multiple people.</li><li><strong>If a carer is identified:</strong><ul><li>Record their details on the patient records (if the patient is registered with the practice and the patient and carer give their consent). </li><li>Record carer status on their own records (if the carer is registered with the practice and the carer gives their consent).</li></ul></li></ul><!-- end field 967dc816-36a2-48a5-bd8b-ac4000b1e436 --><!-- end item d0f7cfa0-ba82-4110-a1ef-ac4000b1e436 -->","topic":{"id":"8a0dcd0d-457e-51f3-bb8d-cb9abed98985","topicId":"535a2cb2-ac55-4c42-ba32-ac4000b1d290","topicName":"Support for adult carers","slug":"support-for-adult-carers","lastRevised":"November 2020","chapters":[{"id":"c8031010-eeca-5ec2-8a2b-5fb3ca2eb166","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"69ec7c8f-cf0d-5dbd-b893-89c2650a72ca","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"49a3aecb-d0b2-58e2-8ec3-fe94f2a9132b","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"936b3c23-1c2f-5003-9f5d-05e063485d44","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"77adc050-2665-545f-89b0-60ee6b0c8116","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"6a2556ad-0860-52f0-a8a0-c57cd81f9263","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"edeeef30-2db3-5c88-8e49-e79f62b6fd87","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"b9e9f803-c81a-59fb-81b0-3e9fcbd97741","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"118bcee7-0fd7-5dad-954c-1746972d2785","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"90a67215-579b-5c33-9bbe-623f00a74969","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"e809a3f4-6c60-5381-a80f-e1cebb45f95a","slug":"nice-quality-standards","fullItemName":"NICE quality standards"},{"id":"64e6b8a1-4285-552a-a894-4fb4b7bb0b17","slug":"qipp","fullItemName":"QIPP"}]},{"id":"f34fb066-09ab-5503-93fb-fadba45fa824","fullItemName":"Background information","slug":"background-information","subChapters":[{"id":"ef6815d9-22a5-5ee6-bdee-c9966934faa6","slug":"definition","fullItemName":"Definition"},{"id":"5d4708a6-fed5-5df6-a61b-6a174317fc0a","slug":"prevalence","fullItemName":"Prevalence"},{"id":"ddaba137-c888-5ff1-bf6a-f53d184ff248","slug":"challenges-experienced-by-carers","fullItemName":"Challenges experienced by carers"},{"id":"6dbe6315-0fab-5dd4-a8ad-069d04509344","slug":"identifying-supporting-carers","fullItemName":"Identifying and supporting carers"}]},{"id":"1a6af021-fb7e-5c66-acde-64d63d957561","fullItemName":"Diagnosis","slug":"diagnosis","subChapters":[{"id":"fdbb1671-2bdc-57f0-81c5-e2e9d29e630e","slug":"identification-of-carers","fullItemName":"Identification of carers"}]},{"id":"71814743-636b-5c02-ac46-4591757d9596","fullItemName":"Management","slug":"management","subChapters":[{"id":"7e7b3147-dd06-5a7a-b31b-9c6308101e23","slug":"management","fullItemName":"Scenario: Management"}]},{"id":"f1647cb9-c52a-5ca9-9803-39bae5e49004","fullItemName":"Supporting evidence","slug":"supporting-evidence","subChapters":[]},{"id":"9a5a5b66-2cd0-54e8-8b71-b30f7804155f","fullItemName":"How this topic was developed","slug":"how-this-topic-was-developed","subChapters":[{"id":"0a4b6a72-fd57-5def-bd99-a2389f0ed876","slug":"search-strategy","fullItemName":"Search strategy"},{"id":"38914d51-a2ad-5908-80e0-4761f9306e28","slug":"stakeholder-engagement","fullItemName":"Stakeholder engagement"},{"id":"f9f3c9c8-020e-5782-9821-b44616e11be0","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria"},{"id":"8e915040-d70c-5bfb-a659-c5c4f704cdfc","slug":"organizational-behavioural-financial-barriers","fullItemName":"Organizational, behavioural and financial barriers"},{"id":"999b57a0-2af4-5dd7-98a5-1b581bec90c4","slug":"declarations-of-interest","fullItemName":"Declarations of interest"}]},{"id":"869c8365-35cf-553b-a805-5ec246be8c55","fullItemName":"References","slug":"references","subChapters":[]}]},"parentChapter":{"id":"1a6af021-fb7e-5c66-acde-64d63d957561","slug":"diagnosis","fullItemName":"Diagnosis"},"subChapters":[{"id":"5e359950-89f6-531b-ab18-d3f6b18912ad","slug":"basis-for-recommendation-b3c","fullItemName":"Basis for recommendation","depth":3,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 959557ce-d500-4316-b083-ac4000b1e436 --><h3>Basis for recommendation</h3><!-- end field 959557ce-d500-4316-b083-ac4000b1e436 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item b3c7182f-890f-4d5b-a7c4-ac4000b1e436 --><!-- begin field c0b42949-5e57-4a4a-bfee-ac4000b1e436 --><p>Recommendations on identifying carers are based on the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) guideline <em>Supporting adult carers </em>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/support-for-adult-carers/references/\">NICE, 2020</a>] and the Royal College of General Practitioners report <em>Involving and supporting carers and families </em>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/support-for-adult-carers/references/\">RCGP, 2014</a>].</p><ul><li>The primary care team has an essential role in the identification of carers [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/support-for-adult-carers/references/\">NHS England, 2016</a>].<strong> </strong>Identification of carers and understanding their caring situation allows advice, support, and assessment to be provided that are more likely to meet their needs [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/support-for-adult-carers/references/\">NICE, 2020</a>].</li></ul><!-- end field c0b42949-5e57-4a4a-bfee-ac4000b1e436 --><!-- end item b3c7182f-890f-4d5b-a7c4-ac4000b1e436 -->","subChapters":[]}]}}},"staticQueryHashes":["3666801979"]}